The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Australia close in on victory
                                                                                                                       7                                      Australia close in on victory
                      
	Wellington: Doug Bollinger brought New Zealand down to their knees as he Australia took firm control in the first Test in Wellington on Sunday.         
	According to Cricinfo, pacer Bollinger snared five wickets in the first innings to hasten the hosts downfall. In reply to the visitors 459 for five declared, New Zealand managed 157.         
	After Ricky Ponting had enforced the follow on, Daniel Vettoris side were 187 for five in their second innings, at the close of the third days play.         
	New Zealand didnt understand the fuss over Bollinger during the one-day series, but they do now after he put Australia on track for a convincing victory in Wellington. After struggling through the limited-overs engagements and being attacked by the home batsmen, Bollinger has caused a lot of damage on a fine surface during the opening Test.         
	After a career-best five for 28 in the first innings, Bollinger returned to cause more difficulties during the hosts improved second effort.         
	Bollinger has played only seven Tests, but he was the attacks main man as he recorded the second five-wicket haul of his career and followed up with two for 30 off 13 overs.                                                                                                                     
